                  <persName id="t18310908-212-person1586">
                  JOHN 
                  SHELDON
               <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1586" type="surname" value="SHELDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1586" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1586" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18310908-212-viclabel1099" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-212-victim1585 t18310908-212-viclabel1099"></join>, and live in Payne-street, White Conduit-fields. On the 5th of August I sent my little boy to fetch some work from Mr. Lyons, in Amwell-street; he never brought it - I was obliged to pay for it - I do not know the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-212-person1587">
                  RICHARD 
                  SHELDON
               <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1587" type="surname" value="SHELDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1587" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1587" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the son of the prosecutor. I saw Mr. Lyon put this property into my bag; there was one pound of meat, sixteen pieces of leather, and a pair of boots - I was bringing them to my father's, and saw the prisoner in Penton-street; he said he would give me 3d. to go an errand for him - I said I would; he said I must leave my bag with him - I was to fetch him some clothes from the corner of Vittoria-street, and he would take care of my bag - I was not gone above five or ten minutes; they said they had no clothes; when I came back he was gone with the bag - I never had the 3d; on the 19th of August, I saw him by Islington turnpike, and pointed him out to the constable, who took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-212-person1588">
                  JOHN 
                  SHEEHY
               <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1588" type="surname" value="SHEEHY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1588" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1588" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. The boy pointed the prisoner out at the turnpike, and said he had stolen his bag of work - I followed him; he looked back, and seeing me and the boy, began to run, but I secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-212-person1589">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PRATTERO
               <interp inst="t18310908-212-person1589" type="surname" value="PRATTERO"></interp>
